# Optional: force API origin for fetch + media (img/video) src.
# In `npm run dev` / `npm run preview` on a VPS, leave unset so the browser uses same-origin `/v1`
# (Vite proxies to FastAPI on this machine). Production behind nginx: also leave unset — nginx proxies `/v1`.
# Only set VITE_API_BASE_URL when the SPA and API are on different origins; then set API
# CORS_EXTRA_ORIGINS (repo `.env`) to include your Studio origin. Never use http://127.0.0.1:8000
# if users open the UI from another host or https:// (that address is the visitor's PC, not your server).
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com

# Optional: Firebase web config (shows "Continue with Google" when repo-root .env does not expose firebase to the API).
# Values are in Firebase Console → Project settings → Your apps → Web app. API must still have
# DIRECTOR_FIREBASE_CREDENTIALS_PATH for POST /v1/auth/firebase to succeed.
# VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
# VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
# VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
# VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
